parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brakes can cause a loss of stopping power, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
brake pedal travels further than usual
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
vehicle pulls to one side when braking
brake warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leak from the governor housing can cause the vehicle to lose engine oil, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a fire. This can also lead to premature wear on engine components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the bolt hole on the side of the governor housing
oil stains under the vehicle
low engine oil levels
engine noise or knocking sounds
increased engine temperature.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transfer case problem can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver. This can also lead to premature wear on drivetrain components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting into four-wheel drive
loss of power to the wheels
unusual noises or vibrations from the transfer case
difficulty engaging or disengaging four-wheel drive
warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system short circuit can cause battery failure, leading to a loss of power to critical vehicle systems, including the engine, lights, and safety features, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery drains rapidly
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
the vehicle's lights or accessories fail to operate
the vehicle's engine stalls or fails to start
a burning smell or smoke is present.
